{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e9b336a7-d2e3-464f-aa48-4de03ed8151c","content":"Yes, you'll hit **framework compatibility issues**. MSTest v3 dropped support for older TFMs. Looking at your project:\n\n| Target | MSTest v3 Support |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ **Dropped** — requires .NET 6+ |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ **Dropped** — requires .NET 6+ |\n\n**To migrate, you'd need to:**\n\n1. Replace `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` with `net6.0` or later.\n2. Replace the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages with the single **`MSTest`** meta-package (v3+).\n\nIf you still need to test against `netcoreapp3.1` or `net5.0`, you'll have to stay on MSTest v2 for those targets. Want me to update the project?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5fc81db6-73a7-4a84-a20c-8e53223f7818","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate to MSTest v3. Let me think about what compatibility issues they might face.\n\nMSTest v3 dropped support for older target frameworks. Specifically:\n- MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+ or .NET Framework 4.6.2+\n- `netcoreapp3.1` is no longer supported in MSTest v3\n- `net5.0` is also no longer supported in MSTest v3\n- `net462` should still be supported\n\nSo the main compatibility issues are:\n\n\n- `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` won't work with MSTest v3, but `net462` is fine\n- There's also a packaging change where they can consolidate to the single `MSTest` meta-package instead of managing separate framework and adapter packages","outputTokens":519,"requestId":"CFCC:1CA5E9:61478A6:6D5ECD3:69EC270D"},"id":"84bf1c4f-65ae-4939-8fa3-b3d922594792","timestamp":"2026-04-25T02:29:43.593Z","parentId":"70511b83-2838-4fb4-a62c-b4b755f5f6c9"}
